SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c02810240
Version: 1

HPSBMA02668 SSRT100474 rev.1 - HP OpenView Storage Data Protector, Remote Execution of Arbitrary Code

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2011-04-28
Last Updated: 2011-04-28

 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Potential Security Impact: Remote execution of arbitrary code

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
Potential security vulnerabilities have been identified with HP OpenView Storage Data Protector. These vulnerabilities could be remotely exploited to execute arbitrary code.

References:

ZDI-CAN-1171 / CVE-2011-1728

ZDI-CAN-1172 / CVE-2011-1729

ZDI-CAN-1173 / CVE-2011-1730

ZDI-CAN-1174 / CVE-2011-1731

ZDI-CAN-1175 / CVE-2011-1732

ZDI-CAN-1176 / CVE-2011-1733

ZDI-CAN-1177 / CVE-2011-1734

ZDI-CAN-1178 / CVE-2011-1735

ZDI-CAN-1179 / CVE-2011-1736

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP OpenView Storage Data Protector v6.00, v6.10, and v6.11 running on Windows.

BACKGROUND

